Rapid Wien Player Hits Tinder To Find ‘Model’ On Two-Day Europa League Trip To Milan

Rapid Wien midfielder Philipp Schobesberger is likely to feature for the Austrian club in their Europa League round of 32 second leg against Inter Milan on Thursday night.

The 25-year-old, who has scored just once this season, will be hoping to make an impact at the San Siro tomorrow night as the Austrian Bundesliga side trail 1-0.

But even if his side fail to quality for the next round, Schobesberger may find comfort elsewhere.

Thanks to someone on dating website Tinder who took a screenshot of Schobesberger's profile, we have discovered that the midfielder is "looking for a model" while on his two-day trip to Milan.
He's not messing around either. The 25-year-old states that "he's only in Milan for two days so better be quick." - you've charmed me.

The Austrian international has also tactically changed his profile picture to a snap of him in action against Milan last week.
